cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper is about few-shot learning for image classification, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a method that involves learning object-level representations and using them to improve few-shot learning, which is a technique that falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using nearest neighbor search, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG and cs.AI. The other two sub-categories are less likely but still possible given the techniques used in the paper.
